    "client_msg_id": "a2ab209e-d56d-438e-b595-dd3c2ae6d5f6",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Very true. Most debuggers I used are a big source of frustration and the only reason to use them is having no other choice. My personal ranking is:\n1. Smalltalk: debugger OK (but could be improved)\n2. Python: a bit primitive in the base language, but OK with a GUI layer on top of it. But could be improved quite a bit.\n3. Everything else: frustrating. I never seem to be able to get at the information I want, usually because too much meta-information has been thown away by some compiler.",
